verbose_text: Under oxidative stress, FoxO is activated to competitively bind to beta-catenin and translocate into the nucleus, resulting in the shift of limited beta-catenin in the Wnt / beta-catenin pathway from beta-catenin / TCF-mediated transcription to FoxO mediated transcription, thereby reducing Osteoblasts proliferate and differentiate and eventually form oxidative stress induced osteoporosis XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR.
